<subSubSection id="A7CC2DBDFFD4FFFFFF6BFD1BFEF7FAA4" pageId="14" pageNumber="289" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="EF697E36FFD4FFFFFF6BFD1BFE2CFCC4" blockId="14.[151,1127,765,1396]" pageId="14" pageNumber="289">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFD4FFFFFF6BFD1BFEB8FCA4" bold="true" box="[151,262,765,788]" pageId="14" pageNumber="289">Remarks.</emphasis>
Both taxa were described in the same book by 
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFD4FFFFFCFEFD1BFC0AFCA4" author="BOHEMAN" box="[770,948,765,788]" firstAuthor="BOHEMAN" pageId="14" pageNumber="289" refId="ref47955" refString="BOHEMAN C. H. 1855: Monographia Cassididarum. Tomus Tertius. Officina Norstedtiana, Holmiae, 543 pp. + 1 pl." type="book" year="1855">BOHEMAN (1855)</bibRefCitation>
just a few pages apart. 
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFD4FFFFFF27FCFBFECDFC84" author="SPAETH" box="[219,371,797,820]" firstAuthor="SPAETH" pageId="14" pageNumber="289" refId="ref50998" refString="SPAETH F. 1914: Chrysomelidae: 16. Cassidinae. In: SCHENKLING S. (ed.): Coleopterorum Catalogus. Pars 62. W. Junk, Berlin, 180 pp." type="book" year="1914">SPAETH (1914)</bibRefCitation>
transferred both to 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFD4FFFFFDB4FCFBFCD1FC84" authority="Boheman, 1854" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1854" box="[584,879,797,820]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Charidotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="289" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFD4FFFFFDB4FCFBFD04FC84" box="[584,698,797,820]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="289">Charidotis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFD4FFFFFD3EFCFBFCD1FC84" author="Boheman" box="[706,879,797,820]" firstAuthor="Boheman" pageId="14" pageNumber="289" refId="ref47930" refString="BOHEMAN C. H. 1854: Monographia Cassididarum. Tomus Secundus. Officina Norstedtiana, Holmiae, 506 pp. + 2 pls." type="book" year="1854">Boheman, 1854</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFD4FFFFFC86FCFBFBACFC84" author="SPAETH" box="[890,1042,797,820]" firstAuthor="SPAETH" pageId="14" pageNumber="289" pagination="66 - 99" refId="ref51359" refString="SPAETH F. 1936: Bestimmungstabelle der Gattung Charidotis (Col. Chrys. Cassid.). Sbornik Entomologickeho Oddeleni Narodniho Musea v Praze 14: 66 - 99." type="journal article" year="1936">SPAETH (1936)</bibRefCitation>
revised the genus and separated the two taxa only by colour: 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFD4FFFFFD34FCDBFCF2FCE4" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1855" box="[712,844,829,852]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="289" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="annularis">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFD4FFFFFD34FCDBFCF2FCE4" box="[712,844,829,852]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="289">C. annularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with red disc of elytra and 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFD4FFFFFF6BFCBBFEAAFCC4" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1855" box="[151,276,861,884]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="289" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="signoreti">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFD4FFFFFF6BFCBBFEAAFCC4" box="[151,276,861,884]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="289">C. signoreti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with black.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EF697E36FFD4FFFFFF49FC9BFD34FB24" blockId="14.[151,1127,765,1396]" pageId="14" pageNumber="289">
Examination of both types as well as additional historic specimens from various institutions revealed that the colour of elytra is variable in these taxa. Even the 
<typeStatus id="306DC094FFD4FFFFFC8DFC7BFC7AFC04" box="[881,964,925,948]" pageId="14" pageNumber="289">syntype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFD4FFFFFC15FC7BFBD9FC04" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1855" box="[1001,1127,925,948]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="289" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="signoreti">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFD4FFFFFC15FC7BFBD9FC04" box="[1001,1127,925,948]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="289">C. signoreti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has variegated elytra, basally and centrally more black and laterally reddish-brown. Uniformly black specimens are very rare in collections and as result 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFD4FFFFFCDEFC3BFC1FFC44" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1855" box="[802,929,989,1012]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="289" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="signoreti">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFD4FFFFFCDEFC3BFC1FFC44" box="[802,929,989,1012]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="289">C. signoreti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was listed only in catalogues while 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFD4FFFFFEAFFC1BFE64FBA4" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1855" box="[339,474,1021,1044]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="289" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="annularis">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFD4FFFFFEAFFC1BFE64FBA4" box="[339,474,1021,1044]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="289">C. annularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was repeatedly reported (see 
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFD4FFFFFCDCFC1BFC6AFBA4" author="BOROWIEC" box="[800,980,1021,1044]" firstAuthor="BOROWIEC" pageId="14" pageNumber="289" refId="ref48283" refString="BOROWIEC L. 1999 a: A world catalogue of the Cassidinae (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae). Biologica Silesiae, Wroclaw, 476 pp." type="book" year="1999" yearSuffix="a">BOROWIEC 1999a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFD4FFFFFC1DFC1BFED5FB84" author="BOROWIEC &amp; SWIETOJANSKA" firstAuthor="BOROWIEC" pageId="14" pageNumber="289" refId="ref48617" refString="BOROWIEC L. &amp; SWIETOJANSKA J. 2016: Cassidinae of the world - an interactive manual (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae). Permanent electronic publication available from: http: // culex. biol. uni. wroc. pl / cassidae / katalog % 20 internetowy / index. htm (last accessed on 18 th May 2016)." type="url" year="2016">BOROWIEC &amp; ŚWIĘTOJAŃSKA 2016</bibRefCitation>
). In my opinion both nominal taxa represent colour morphs of a single species as all other morphological characters are identical. Such variability in colouration is not uncommon in similar species of 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFD4FFFFFDE8FBBBFD38FBC4" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1854" box="[532,646,1117,1140]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Charidotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="289" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFD4FFFFFDE8FBBBFD38FBC4" box="[532,646,1117,1140]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="289">Charidotis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and it is known for instance in 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFD4FFFFFC30FBBBFEFEFB24" authority="Boheman, 1855" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1855" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Charidotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="289" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="auroguttata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFD4FFFFFC30FBBBFBD8FBC4" box="[972,1126,1117,1140]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="289">C. auroguttata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFD4FFFFFF6BFB9BFEFEFB24" author="Boheman" box="[151,320,1149,1172]" firstAuthor="Boheman" pageId="14" pageNumber="289" refId="ref47955" refString="BOHEMAN C. H. 1855: Monographia Cassididarum. Tomus Tertius. Officina Norstedtiana, Holmiae, 543 pp. + 1 pl." type="book" year="1855">Boheman, 1855</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFD4FFFFFE88FB9BFD38FB24" authority="Spaeth, 1902" authorityName="Spaeth" authorityYear="1902" box="[372,646,1149,1172]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Charidotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="289" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="porosula">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFD4FFFFFE88FB9BFE4FFB24" box="[372,497,1149,1172]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="289">C. porosula</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFD4FFFFFE04FB9BFD38FB24" author="Spaeth" box="[504,646,1149,1172]" firstAuthor="Spaeth" pageId="14" pageNumber="289" pagination="81 - 102" refId="ref50784" refString="SPAETH F. 1902: Neue Cassiden aus Peru. Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift 1902: 81 - 102." type="journal article" year="1902">Spaeth, 1902</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EF697E36FFD4FFFFFF49FB7BFEF7FAA4" blockId="14.[151,1127,765,1396]" pageId="14" pageNumber="289">
Since both taxa were described in the same publication I followed the Principle of the first reviser (
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFD4FFFFFF13FB5BFED1FB64" author="ICZN" box="[239,367,1213,1236]" firstAuthor="ICZN" pageId="14" pageNumber="289" refId="ref49784" refString="ICZN 1999: International code of zoological nomenclature. Fourth edition. The International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London, xxix + 306 pp." type="book" year="1999">ICZN 1999</bibRefCitation>
: Article 24.2) and chose the name 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFD4FFFFFD1AFB5BFCD3FB64" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1855" box="[742,877,1213,1236]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Coptocycla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="289" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="annularis">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFD4FFFFFD1AFB5BFCD3FB64" box="[742,877,1213,1236]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="289">C. annularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as valid for this taxon, as it has been used recently and the species is more frequently identified in the collections under this name.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
